section.section:
An order to liquidate the business of a domestic insurer shall direct the Commissioner promptly:
to take possession of the property of the insurer;
to liquidate the business of the insurer;
to deal with the property and business of the insurer in the name of the Commissioner or in the name of the insurer, as the court directs; and
to notify all creditors that may have claims against the insurer to present their claims.
